name: SOLD OUT! zhao - made in china (gold)
description:
" idiana's love, as an addiction, made in china, like a cracked dam leaking.

The painting is not a criticism of China at all. It's a criticism of global consumerism. The gravity of greed (economics) pulling us all to offer only the least amount of money for the most exorbitant amount of work and sacrifice.

Look under every thing around you, from toys to toilet bowls, it says Made In China. because it's the cheapest way to have them made.

We make China make them.

For accepting the lowest price (due to lack of choice or greed), China paid a price. From soot filled skies, to toxic waters, to great income disparity and social unjusts.

This re-iteration of Indian's LOVE, using these 4 famous chinese characters, is my western educated eyes witness account of my contact with the place.

This is not a political painting. It's a landscape painting, of a scenery I saw." - zhao

mixed media on
16x20 inch 300gsm watercolor paper

varied 
gold edition of 10

signed, numbered and titled by artist
embossed stamped with Certificate of Authenticity by highly framable

name: SOLD OUT!!! zhao - "NIGHT" GLOBAL NEIGHBOURHOOD WATCH
description:
20 of the ed of 41 will be darker.

Deep red, browns, greens, greens and black as background.

some of which are so dark, an extra screen of grey is given to have the details "pop" a little more.

select this option if you wish to receive a darker edition of the print.

each print comes with free AI THE GIANT stencil

ed of 41. each unique

420 x 297mm 2-3 colour hand painted silkscreen
on very fancy 270gsm cotton paper

Artist's statements:
"the print is my reaction to not just weiwei cam (though that was the starting point) but to the idea of how power has leaked from the government into everyone's hands. Now mighty politicians (and dictators even) have to tip toe around issues, not just in fear of the nosy journalists, but the bored, facebook poking, you-tube cute kitty watching, internet users. it's a reminder of the power we have inherited, and the weiwei iconography is a symbol of the lives we can affect with this power, in a very real and direct way."

zhao:
"i've decided to make each print unique. each print will be in its own colorway. each with different stencil and spray paint elements. I want each to look like prints on very old and decayed walls with hints of old paint smudges from weather and pollution, and marks from previous stencils. sorry to those who wanted the CMYK versions, not making them anymore."

on AI THE GIANT stencil:

"i'm very proud of the stencil. i wanted it to be as minimalist and iconic as shepard fairey's Andre, and i stole the word Giant as a nod to the guy I stole the whole look from. So yes, this is a two-artwork-in-one release. Ghost mini prints used an older cut. a different, thinner one, made for spray painting blotchy chunks on paper. There was only one stencil made for Ghost mini prints.
This edition has a different cut, and material, made for the quick outdoor use, sturdy and back-pack friendly.
You can frame it of course, but I do hope people would use it for a while before framing. Trust me, it'll look much cooler with sprayed colors on."

name: SOLD OUT! ZHAO - AI THE GIANT stencil #1
description:
AI THE GIANT STENCIL #1
A project – for ai weiwei

zhao wishes sincerely that you would buy and use this laser cut, 3mm acrylic stencil.

Put it against a surface, spray paint, crayon, ink, mud, ice-cream over it. Repeat as often as you like. Do it on walls, floors, trash, fancy art paper, pizza boxes, any thing your heart desires.

Do not vandalised illegally if you’re not prepared to face the full extent of the law. Stay safe, spray on your property, or do it with consent. 

neither Highlyframable nor Zhao is responsible for any illegal action taken by the user. you are on your own.

Once done, take a photo of your work and email it to highlyframable@gmail.com and you could win the last 2 originals of 12 squares by zhao. It's a totally random draw, and the more photos you send in, the better your chances of winning. 

2 winners will be contacted on 4 June 2013.

"Put his face out there. Help promote his existence. Make his face more famous than colonel sanders'. Let the world not forget what Ai is going through, while we eat, shit, shop, sleep, surf, tweet and greet in freedom. Thank you."


This version is limited stock of only 50.

Another version will be up after this one's sold out.

This stencil also comes free with every print by zhao.

GO FORTH! HAVE FUN!


ABOUT AI WEIWEI:

wiki:
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ai_Weiwei

MUST WATCH MOVIE (now showing):
http://www.facebook.com/awwneversorry/timeline

Must watch Youtube clip:
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=37-LG0oAhAs&feature=youtu.be&a

Must follow Twitter feed:
https://twitter.com/#!/aiww

It's in Chinese, just cut and paste into google translate and get a rough idea of what's been spoken.

http://translate.google.com/

Due to strong censorship, Ai's blog hasn't been active. Following his twitter feed is more than just getting daily updates, it's a way of letting the people in charge know, the world is watching. Every pair of eyes help.
 

"Ai Weiwei is my art god. His work seems to be made not for money or fame, but for the people. Though he is obviously much more, he seems to share the same ethos of a true street artist. Making emotive political statements, in the most striking, and beautiful way, and unlike most of his pompous high-end contemporaries, he makes them huge and free and out there, on the streets, inside free museums, for the people, to touch, to sit on, to step on, to steal from, to become part of. Ai Weiwei's life is in danger. Every tweet, email, film, exhibit he does, is bringing embarrassment to the people who are trying to shut him up. Possibly as permanently as they can. But he won't shut up. And neither should we." - zhao
